    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - HEATER AND AIR CONDITIONER BLOWER WITH THERMOSTAT
        TEMPERATURE CONTROL (SLEEPER) - TROUBLESHOOTING - THERMOSTAT TEMPERATURE CONTROL (SLEEPER)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>THERMOSTAT TEMPERATURE CONTROL (SLEEPER)</title>
        <table id="t0828403" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Thermostat Temperature Control (Sleeper)</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.70in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.78in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.44in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (552), and move key switch to ignition position. At (522) circuit
                                75AL, measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(552), 75AL to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75AL, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>At connector (552) measure voltage from circuit 75L to 75-GS.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(552), 75L to 75-GS.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 75-GS, conn. (552), circuit 75-GS, 11-GBJ,
                                11-GAN, conn. (81), or cir. 11-GBB to right cab ground stud (404), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>Bench test automatic temperature control by applying +12 volts to pin "A" at conn.
                                (552), applying ground to pin "C" and measuring voltage at pin "B" to ground. Measure
                                voltage at pin "B" while turning control knob full CCW, then fully CW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(552), term. B to C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>Full CCW: 12 volts, full CW: 0 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective automatic temperature control module.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>With bench test wiring still installed, and control knob set to center of range, does
                                output voltage at pin "B" change as warm or cool air is applied to the ambient air
                                sensor?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(552), term. B to C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>0 to 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective automatic temperature control module.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>Reconnect connector (552), disconnect conn. (45), move key switch to ignition
                                position, and at (45) circuit 75K [going to (80)] measure voltage to ground while
                                rotating sleeper temperature control fully CCW and CW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(45), 75K to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>2V and 11V.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75K, conn. (80) or circuit 75K, then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>At connector (45) measure voltage from circuit 75L [coming from (441)] to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(45), 75L to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75L, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>Reconnect connector (45). Does heater box damper door function properly?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to Step 16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect heater box damper conn. (N/L), and with key switch in ignition position,
                                measure voltage from circuit 75L to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(N/L), 75L to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75L, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>At heater box damper connector (N/L), measure voltage from circuit 75L to 75-GL.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(N/L), 75L to 75-GL.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 75-GL, 75-G, or 11-G to right cab ground
                                stud (404), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>At heater box damper connector (N/L), measure voltage from circuit 75K to ground while
                                rotating sleeper temperature control fully CCW and CW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(N/L), 75K to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>2V and 11V.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75K, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>Reconnect heater box damper conn. (N/L), move key switch to ignition position, and
                                move sleeper blower switch. (550) to low speed position. Note if damper door closes
                                completely and opens completely, when the sleeper temperature control is moved fully CW
                                and CCW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Sleeper temperature control circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective damper motor assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
